'''Louis Etienne Jean Léonce Balluet d'Estournelles de Constant Rebecque''' (15 September 1859 – 31 July 1949) was a [[sailor]] from [[France]],<ref name="A" /> who represented his country at the [[Sailing at the 1900 Summer Olympics – .5 to 1 ton|1900 Summer Olympics]] in [[Meulan]], [[France]]. Jean d'Estournelles de Constant as helmsman, took the 5th place in first race of the [[Ton class|0.5 to 1 ton]] and did not finished in the second race. He did this with the boat ''Pierre et Jean''.

